most of the enemies aren't implemented yet. Only the 1st stage is full of enemies, stage 2 has only part of them done and other has no enemies, only glitchy bosses that doensn't work and make the game crash. Only the area close to the last boss is not yet designed - that is because I'll see in which of the CHR-ROM bank there's space left for the final boss so the design will vary depending on that. There's basically no in-game plot, and there probably won't be. I was almost going to include mini dialogue before and/or after boss fights at the end of each level, but I gave up on that idea since 1) ROM size is limited and 2) I didn't know what most boss would say and for non-humanoid bosses it would have been weird to see them talking.<br /><br />By the way my gmae *is* going to have the RPG elements Tokumaru was talking about, but I'll try to make grinding un-necessary. It'll be up to the player whether they want to spend time grinding and have an easy time beating the bosses, or rather making progress fast and have harder action. The details will have to be fixed in the testing phase though (if I ever go there !).</div>

